<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFCB3355FF6CF9177602FA04" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="215" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" type="description">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFCB3355FF6CF9177619FB64" blockId="19.[176,1235,1749,1840]" lastBlockId="20.[166,1225,1153,1436]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="215" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">
D i a g n o s i s. 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCB3352FE07F9177015F977" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1934" box="[398,550,1749,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Prohypotyphla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCB3352FE07F9177393F977" box="[398,416,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCB3352FE25F9147015F977" box="[428,550,1750,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCB3352FD3CF917711EF977" authorityName="Hendel V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[693,813,1749,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCB3352FD3CF91770F4F977" box="[693,711,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCB3352FD5DF917711EF977" box="[724,813,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCB3352FCEDF91771E3F977" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[868,976,1749,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCB3352FCEDF9177145F977" box="[868,886,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCB3352FC0AF91771E3F977" box="[899,976,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the group of species represented by reddish-yellow, large flies with elongated pedicel and flagellomere 1 (latter parallel-sided, twice as long as wide and apically blunt), lacking outer vertical setae, moderately long body, setose mid and hind coxae, short preapical ventral setae on mid and hind femur, short setulose scutellum with 4 scutellar setae, easily differing from all known 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCC3355FC4CFB637665FB23" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[965,1110,1185,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FC4CFB637665FB23" box="[965,1110,1185,1211]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by almost entirely dark brown wing (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FE43FB037023FB44" box="[458,528,1217,1244]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[165,198,1041,1063]" captionTargetBox="[336,1043,174,1018]" captionTargetId="figure-351@20.[336,1043,174,1042]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 22. Campylocera nigripennis: holotype ♀ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 —head, left; 3 — head, anterior view; 4 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 5 — fore and mid coxae; 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior; 7 — mid coxa, femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — hind coxae; 9 — abdomen, ventrolateral view; 10 —wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453751/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">fig. 22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FD90FB037007FB43" box="[537,564,1217,1243]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[166,199,1778,1800]" captionTargetBox="[255,1063,1151,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-429@10.[246,1073,1138,1759]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 10. Campylocera latigenis: holotype Ơ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, right; 4 — head, dorsal view; 5 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453716/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FD90FB037007FB43" box="[537,564,1217,1243]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">10</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), winding vein R 
<subScript id="C26E5C32FFCC3355FD66FB16713BFB7A" attach="left" box="[751,776,1236,1250]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">2+3</subScript>
, facial carina wide and low, ocellar, postocellar, anterior notopleural and katepisternal setae lacking. Wing length 9.2 mm.
</paragraph>
<caption id="0A950EFFFFCC3355FF2CFBD3761BFBC4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453751" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453751/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" startId="20.[165,198,1041,1063]" targetBox="[336,1043,174,1018]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFCC3355FF2CFBD3761BFBC4" blockId="20.[165,1225,1039,1116]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
Fig. 22. 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCC3355FF79FBD373EEFBBF" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[240,477,1041,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FF79FBD373EEFBBF" box="[240,477,1041,1063]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Campylocera nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: holotype ♀ (NHMW): 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FD4DFBD370FCFBBE" box="[708,719,1041,1062]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">1</emphasis>
— habitus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FC33FBD371F6FBBE" box="[954,965,1041,1062]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">2</emphasis>
—head, left; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FBCAFBD3767DFBBE" box="[1091,1102,1041,1062]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">3</emphasis>
— head, anterior view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FE9EFBEE7311FBD9" box="[279,290,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">4</emphasis>
— mesonotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FDBEFBEE7071FBD9" box="[567,578,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">5</emphasis>
— fore and mid coxae; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FCABFBEE711EFBD9" box="[802,813,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">6</emphasis>
— fore femur and tibia, posterior; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FBFEFBEE76B1FBD9" box="[1143,1154,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">7</emphasis>
— mid coxa, femur and tibia, anterior; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FE5FFB8573D2FBC4" box="[470,481,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">8</emphasis>
— hind coxae; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FDFFFB8570B2FBC4" box="[630,641,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">9</emphasis>
— abdomen, ventrolateral view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FC36FB8571E5FBC4" box="[959,982,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">10</emphasis>
—wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFCC3355FF52FAC37602FA04" blockId="20.[166,1225,1153,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
R e m a r k. Known from a unique male only, this species is believed to belong in the group of species, which includes 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCC3355FDB9FAE070BEFAA3" box="[560,653,1313,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewi">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FDB9FAE07070FAA4" box="[560,579,1314,1340]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FDD8FAE370BEFAA3" box="[593,653,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">loewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCC3355FD15FAE0712FFAA3" authorityName="Hendel V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[668,796,1313,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FD15FAE0709CFAA4" box="[668,687,1314,1340]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FD37FAE3712FFAA3" box="[702,796,1313,1339]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related species, differing by the numerous autapomorphic characters (low facial carina, ocellar and anterior notopleural setae lacking, wing dark brown). Otherwise it fits the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCC3355FC01FAA37613FAE3" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[904,1056,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FC01FAA37613FAE3" box="[904,1056,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its essential characters, and I synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCC3355FD8DFA4371B0FA04" authority="Enderlein, 1942" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1942" box="[516,899,1409,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Lygiohypotyphla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FD8DFA4370F7FA03" box="[516,708,1409,1435]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">Lygiohypotyphla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFCC3355FD43FA4371B0FA04" author="Enderlein, G." box="[714,899,1409,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" pagination="98 - 134" refId="ref11407" refString="Enderlein, G. 1942. Klassifikation der Pyrgotiden. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschenden Freunde zu Berlin, (1941) (2), 98 - 134." type="journal article" year="1942">Enderlein, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FC03FA437180FA03" bold="true" box="[906,947,1409,1435]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FC49FA4371E2FA03" bold="true" box="[960,977,1409,1435]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">n</emphasis>
. with it.
</paragraph>
